Marv Albert Joins CBS Sports as Play-by-Play Announcer on NFL Telecasts

-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 
2011-06-06T18:24:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/marv-albert-joins-cbs-sports-as-play-by-play-announcer-on-nfl-telecasts.html
Marv Albert is bringing “Yesss!”
back to the  National Football League .  Albert, 69, has joined  CBS Sports  as a play-by-play 
announcer on NFL telecasts, the network announced today.  Albert’s catchphrase of “Yesss!” has been heard on
broadcasts of football, basketball, hockey and even Wimbledon
tennis. He did NFL games on NBC for 19 years and was the play-
by-play voice of league games on Westwood One radio’s “Monday
Night Football” from 2002 through 2009.  Albert’s son Kenny is an NFL play-by-play announcer on News
Corp.’s Fox network.  CBS announced Albert’s hiring in a news release. Terms of
the deal weren’t disclosed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  